    "changes": [
      "Each legendary achievement now unlocks a unique, exclusive ship you can commission once you've earned it — no piloting rank required to fly it.",
      "Faction legendary ships are available to **every member** of a faction that has earned the achievement, so factions can issue them to new pilots.",
      "Prestige ships are bound to their owner: they can't be sold, listed, gifted, or donated, and they don't count toward \"own every ship class.\"",
      "New hulls include the **Midas** (a gold-drenched billionaire's yacht), the **Comet** (an all-first-class express liner that runs at the speed cap), the **Polymath** (a do-everything Solarian multirole), the **Reliquary** (a fleet carrier with the largest ship bay in the game), and the faction fleet vehicles **Ledger**, **Runner**, **Workhorse**, and **Lone Star**."
